	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=28999><span id= >Domnall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>198 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>These reasons are factual, but it really depends on what the buyer is actually willing to pay when you figure out the final price tag....<br><br>It's pricetag is loosely based on three things.<br>1) It is equippable in either hand.<br>2) +5 Charisma is not too shabby.&nbsp;&nbsp;It makes sales prices raise modestly, and when you are heading into town with that pack chock full`o`stuff for a merchant, the difference in change can mean 10 or 15 extra plat by the time you are through selling everything you are carrying.<br>3) The weapon appeals to a slightly bigger audience than the Ebon Razor, considering the Razor can't be used by Rangers, while the GSS is anything that can use 1HS.  With a bigger market, there is potentially a higher demand for the weapon.<br><br>Again, this is only conjecture.  The prices on the site also may or may not reflect current actual server prices.  Take a look in your main market zone for your server and do a price check.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
